                  <div class="bodytext contentText"> <p>Winter is a high-demand energy month, especially when you have your gas or electric furnace running continuously. If you want to lower the amount you spend over the winter, you can use these professional tips to drive down those costs and put more savings in the bank.</p><p><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Tips for Reducing Energy Consumption with Your HVAC and Furnace in Winnipeg</span><br>It does not matter the size of your home or how often you use your HVAC system; there are always opportunities to reduce energy consumption. If you are unsure where to start, here are a few ways to save:<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">• Have Your Unit Inspected for Efficiency Deficiencies:</span> One of the most important ways to save is having your unit inspected. Professionals know what to look for to ensure optimal efficiency. Furthermore, they can clean out your unit, which may be the root cause of your efficiency issues in the first place. Lastly, having everything repaired ensures your furnace is not working over time, which means less energy spent keeping your house warm.<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">• Focus on the Temperature Settings:</span> If you are gone all day, there is no reason to have your home heated to a temperature you would while you are home. Instead, lower the temperature and use the program feature to have the temperature rise when it is close to the time you come home. Also, set it a few degrees cooler at night, while you are asleep and under blankets anyway. <br><span style="font-weight: bold;">• Change Your Filter Regularly:</span> Furnace filters that are overly dirty can eventually clog the system and make your gas furnace in Winnipeg work harder than necessary; thus, using more energy.<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">• Upgrade to an Energy-Efficient Unit:</span> Depending on how old your furnace is, you could <a href="//<?php echo $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME']; ?>/furnace-repair-replacement-winnipeg" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">replace your existing furnace</a> to save on energy costs. Generally, a furnace lasts your home 10 to 15 years – depending on how well it is maintained and a few other factors. Therefore, if yours is nearing the end of its lifespan, upgrading before winter hits could be an excellent way to save yourself not only monthly heating costs but also potential headaches later.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Upgrade Your Gas Furnace or Schedule Your Furnace Cleaning in Winnipeg Today</span><br>If you are ready to upgrade your furnace, or you would like to schedule an annual cleaning to help save on heating costs this winter, contact the team at <a href="/" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">East Side Ventilation</a>. We offer yearly maintenance, repairs, and we can help find the right furnace for your home when it is time to replace your current one.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Schedule your cleaning or inquire about our new gas furnaces in Winnipeg and surrounding cities here at East Side Ventilation. Call us today at <span data-global="phone">204-667-8700</span> or <a href="/winnipeg-hvac-company-contact" data-track-event="click" data-track-action="internal_link_clicked">contact us</a> online to set up a consultation.</span></p> </div>
